# Google Agenda Sync {#google}

Copy and paste this Calendar link on your browser:

<code id="cal-link">https://e-rotaract.com/calendar/add</code>

Make sure you are logged in the correct Google acount (check the image on the top-right corner of the window)

***If it is not the correct Google account***, select the correct account by clicking the image on the top-right corner

In the pop-up meassage that appears on your screen, click "Add"

# iPhone Calendar Sync {#iphone}

These instructions must be followed in your iPhone, and they will add the club calendar in the iPhone Calendar <img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/png;base64," />

## Step 1

Copy and paste this Calendar link in your <img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /> Safari browser:

<code id="cal-link">https://e-rotaract.com/calendar/add</code>

{% include gallery-btn
  large=FALSE
  items='[
    { name: "Copy Calendar Link", icon: "fas fa-copy fa-lg", url: "javascript:navigator.clipboard.writeText($(\'#cal-link\').text())" },
    { name: "Open Calendar Link", icon: "fas fa-window-restore fa-lg", url: "javascript:window.open($(\'#cal-link\').text());window.location.reload();" }
  ]'
%}

## Step 2

Make sure you are logged in the correct Google acount (check the image on the top-right corner of the window)

***If it is not the correct Google account***, select the correct account by clicking the image on the top-right corner

In the pop-up meassage that appears on your screen, click "Add"

## Step 3

Now, copy and paste this Google link in your <img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /> Safari browser:

<code id="cal-sync">https://calendar.google.com/calendar/syncselect</code>

{% include gallery-btn
  large=false
  items='[
    { name: "Copy Google Link", icon: "fas fa-copy fa-lg", url: "javascript:navigator.clipboard.writeText($(\'#cal-sync\').text())" },
    { name: "Open Google Link", icon: "fas fa-window-restore fa-lg", url: "javascript:window.open($(\'#cal-sync\').text());window.location.reload();" }
  ]'
%}

## Step 4

You must now activate the club calendar by clicking its checkmark âœ…

Remember to save the new settings

## Step 5

On your iPhone, open the <img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /> Settings app

Scroll down until you see <img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/png;base64," /> Calendar, click on it and then select "Accounts"

Check if you have already added the correct Google account, if not click on "Add Account" and add it

Inside the Google account, be sure that the "<img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/png;base64," /> Calendars" option is active

## Step 6

On your iPhone, open the <img style="max-height: 30px; max-width: 30px; padding: 0;" src="data:image/png;base64," /> Calendar app

Click on "Calendars", at the center-bottom of the screen

Activate the club calendar by clicking its checkmark âœ…
